DEM data analysis

Lesson Goals¶

In this lesson i will walk you through how to analyze Digital Elevation Model(DEM) and we save it as a GIS shapefile . We will also visualize the slope aspect ratio which is very crucial finding for land development

Prerequests¶

  1. Install rasterio
  2. Install geopandas
  3. Install shapely

  4. install richdem

    NB:you can collect the dataset from EarthData NASA website

generate a dictionary of the following lists:¶

  • geometry point objects (shapely geomteries)
  • Attributes : elvation, slope, and aspect
In [24]:
pnt_data = {'elevation':[],'slope':[],'aspect':[],'geometry':[]}

width_step = 7
height_step = 200

for i in range(0,raster_width,width_step):
    if i % 47 == 0 and i != 0:
        for j in range(200,raster_height-height_step,height_step):
            pnt_data['elevation'].append(round(maryland_richdem[i,j],2))
            pnt_data['slope'].append(round(maryland_rich_slope[i,j],2))
            pnt_data['aspect'].append(round(maryland_rich_aspect[i,j],2))
            pnt_data['geometry'].append(Point(maryland_rio_ds.xy(i,j)))

Create a geopandas dataframe from the dictionary¶

In [25]:
gp_df = gpd.GeoDataFrame(pnt_data, crs="EPSG:4326")

export the geopandas datafrane to geojson¶

In [26]:
gp_df.to_file('./random_pnts.geojson', driver="GeoJSON")

export the geopandas datafrane to shapefile¶

In [27]:
gp_df.to_file('./random_pnts.shp', driver="ESRI Shapefile")

7. Conclusion¶

The work described in this notebook is shows how to import DEM and analysis. Specifically

  • how to know the property of raster file
  • how to create slope and how to create aspect
  • how to generate dictionary and create geodataframe
  • how to save our dataset into shapefile(.shp)
